SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 360 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. If the Department uses artificial intelligence to
4 communicate or interact with a person concerning the
5 administration and collection of any tax, fee, assessment or other
6 amount required by law to be collected or the imposition of
7 disciplinary action, the Department shall ensure that the person is
8 informed that the person is communicating or interacting with
9 artificial intelligence.
10 2. As used in this section, “artificial intelligence” means a
11 machine-based system that can, for a given set of human-defined
12 objectives, make predictions, recommendations or decisions
13 influencing real or virtual environments.
14 Sec. 2. NRS 360.255 is hereby amended to read as follows:
15 360.255 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section and
16 NRS 239.0115, 360.250 and 607.217, the records and files of the
17 Department , including, without limitation, any records and files
18 that are generated by artificial intelligence used by the
19 Department, concerning the administration or collection of any tax,
20 fee, assessment or other amount required by law to be collected or
21 the imposition of disciplinary action are confidential and privileged.
22 The Department, an employee of the Department and any other
23 person engaged in the administration or collection of any tax, fee,
24 assessment or other amount required by law to be collected or the
25 imposition of disciplinary action or charged with the custody of any
26 such records or files:
27 (a) Shall not disclose any information obtained from those
28 records or files; and
29 (b) May not be required to produce any of the records or files for
30 the inspection of any person or governmental entity or for use in any
31 action or proceeding.
32 2. The records and files of the Department concerning the
33 administration and collection of any tax, fee, assessment or other
34 amount required by law to be collected or the imposition of
35 disciplinary action are not confidential and privileged in the
36 following cases:
37 (a) Testimony by a member or employee of the Department and
38 production of records, files and information on behalf of
39 the Department or a person in any action or proceeding before the
40 Nevada Tax Commission, the State Board of Equalization, the
41 Department, a grand jury or any court in this State if that testimony
